chess
The board should consist of an 8x8 tile board composed of alternating black and white squares
The game supports 2 players
The rank of the opposing sides shall have pieces arranged in a mirrored configuration (like pieces face like pieces)
The back rank pieces consists of: [rook, knight, bishop, queen, king, bishop, knight, rook]
King and queen are swapped according to the rule: queens on their color
The white player starts with their pieces arranged such that the bottom right square is white
Pawns move on tile 'forward' (toward the opposite player's side), except on each pawn's first move, where they may move 2 tiles
Upon reaching the opposite rank they started, a pawn can be promoted to: [rook, knight, bishop, or queen]
A player may not make a move that places their king under attack from an opponent's piece
